FBIS4-39766 "drsov112_c_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-112 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 Federal Assembly Comments on Legislation's `Backwardness' Comments on Legislation's `Backwardness' LD0906143394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0926 GMT 9 Jun 94 LD0906143394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] [Excerpt] Moscow, 9 Jun -- Russian State Duma chairman Ivan Rybkin thinks Boris Yeltsin's decrees on economic reform appeared because of "the known backwardness of Russian legislation." This is what he stated today while opening parliamentary hearings on the strengthening of cooperation between the federal authorities and local state administrative bodies. Ivan Rybkin reported that the important gap in the legislation should be overcome as soon as possible and key legislative acts needed to be adopted for this to happen, including civil and land codes as well as a number of laws on legislation. [passage ommitted]
